text: The Diocese of Visby () is a diocese of the Church of Sweden, established in 1572. Covering Swedish Baltic Sea island of Gotland, it uses the Visby Cathedral as its seat. Since November 2002, the diocese is also responsible for the Church of Sweden Abroad. ==Other websites== * Official website Visby Category:1570s establishments in Europe Category:16th-century establishments in Sweden
